(237, '_transient_owp_feed_data_6c71ead26f51e2ed92c2d54555eeb5fc', '<ul><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://oceanwp.org/blog/oceanwp-theme-panel-makeover/?utm_source=wp-news-widget&utm_medium=wp-dash&utm_campaign=news-feed\' target=\'_blank\'>OceanWP Starboard Update: Our Theme Panel Received a Makeover!</a><div class=\"rssSummary\">Since the Ocean Breeze update, which marked the Spring here at OceanWP, we have been extremely busy working on new improvements for you. Really no use keeping it a secret&hellip;</div></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://oceanwp.org/blog/ocean-breeze-spring-2022-whats-new-in-oceanwp/?utm_source=wp-news-widget&utm_medium=wp-dash&utm_campaign=news-feed\' target=\'_blank\'>Ocean Breeze for Spring 2022: What’s New in OceanWP</a><div class=\"rssSummary\">You need it. Most importantly, you deserve it. The new OceanWP update brings fresh features to enrich your content even without page builders. Enjoy refurbished Ocean Website Templates, royalty-free images,&hellip;</div></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-translate-oceanwp-woocommerce-store/?utm_source=wp-news-widget&utm_medium=wp-dash&utm_campaign=news-feed\' target=\'_blank\'>How to Translate Your OceanWP and WooCommerce Store (the Quick Way)</a><div class=\"rssSummary\">Translating a website used to be time-consuming and expensive. But with a multilingual-ready theme like OceanWP and WPML’s new Translate Everything mode, you can automatically translate your entire store in&hellip;</div></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-dynamic-appointment-website-with-oceanwp-crocoblock/?utm_source=wp-news-widget&utm_medium=wp-dash&utm_campaign=news-feed\' target=\'_blank\'>How to Create a Dynamic Appointment Website with OceanWP &amp; Crocoblock</a><div class=\"rssSummary\">Are you looking to build a dynamic appointment booking website? For those who think it’s hard to deploy, there’s good news – it’s not. Nowadays, you don’t need developers, coders,&hellip;</div></li></ul>', 'no');
